    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// Data process karne ke liye\nconst item = $input.item.json;\n\n// Safe data handling: Agar 'data' field mein response hai to use karein\n// Agar response body direct mil rahi hai to item.json hi rdap hai\nconst rdap = item.data ? (typeof item.data === 'string' ? JSON.parse(item.data) : item.data) : item;\n\n// --- YAHAN HAIN SAFETY CHECKS ---\n// Agar rdap hi nahi bana, to empty object return kardo taake flow na ruke\nif (!rdap || typeof rdap !== 'object') {\n    return { Registrar_Name: \"Error\", Creation_Date: \"N/A\", Expiry_Date: \"N/A\", Domain_Age_Days: \"N/A\" };\n}\n\n// events aur entities ko safely access karein (agar exist na karein to empty array lein)\nconst events = rdap.events || [];\nconst entities = rdap.entities || [];\n\nconst getEvent = (eventsList, action) => eventsList.find(e => e.eventAction === action) || {};\nconst getRegistrar = (entitiesList) => entitiesList.find(e => e.roles && e.roles.includes('registrar')) || {};\n\nconst registration = getEvent(events, 'registration');\nconst expiration = getEvent(events, 'expiration');\nconst registrar = getRegistrar(entities);\n\n// Age calculation\nlet ageInDays = \"N/A\";\nif (registration.eventDate) {\n    const createdDate = new Date(registration.eventDate);\n    const today = new Date();\n    ageInDays = Math.floor((today - createdDate) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24));\n}\n\n// Final output\nreturn {\n  Registrar_Name: (registrar.vcardArray && registrar.vcardArray[1]) ? registrar.vcardArray[1][1][3] : \"N/A\",\n  Creation_Date: registration.eventDate || \"N/A\",\n  Expiry_Date: expiration.eventDate || \"N/A\",\n  Domain_Age_Days: ageInDays\n};"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -16,
        -464
      ],
      "id": "a1e85f31-e9ad-47df-8772-d0414a39683b",
      "name": "Format RDAP Output"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a Cyber-Threat Intelligence Analyst. Your task is to evaluate the legitimacy of a company based on the domain registration data provided.\n\nInput Data:\n- Company Name: {{ $('Get User Input').item.json['Company Name'] }}\n- Domain: {{ $('Unify URL Source').item.json.Cleaned_URL }}\n- Registrar: {{ $json.Registrar_Name }}\n- Registration Date: {{ $json.Creation_Date }}\n- Expiry Date: {{ $json.Expiry_Date }}\n- Domain Age (Days): {{ $json.Domain_Age_Days }}\n\nAssessment Criteria:\n1. Domain Age: If Domain Age is < 180 days (6 months), classify as \"High Risk\".\n2. Name Correlation: Analyze if the Domain name logically relates to the Company Name. If there is zero semantic similarity or if the domain looks random, classify as \"Suspicious\".\n3. Registrar Context: If the registrar name is obscure or known for bulk/cheap domain registration, treat it as a minor risk factor.\n4. Handling Missing Data: If a specific data field is missing or null, do not invent information. Rely only on the available fields to form your verdict.\n\nOutput Requirement:\nReturn ONLY a valid JSON object. Do not include any introductory text, markdown code blocks (like ```json), or explanations outside the JSON.\n\n{\n  \"verdict\": \"Legit\" | \"Suspicious\" | \"High Risk\",\n  \"risk_score\": 0,\n  \"analysis\": \"A concise, single-sentence justification for the verdict.\",\n  \"flagged_issues\": [\"list\", \"of\", \"red\", \"flags\"]\n}\n\nConstraints:\n- Be extremely concise in your 'analysis' field (keep it under 20 words).\n- Do not repeat the input data in your output.\n- Avoid any conversational filler; output raw JSON only.",
        "batching": {}
      },
